This paper discusses the security of sensors in various applications, which falls under the category of computer security (cs.CR). The paper also introduces a system and threat model for signal injection attacks, which involves the interaction between hardware and software systems, making it relevant to the systems and control (cs.SY) and software engineering (cs.SE) sub-categories. The paper also discusses the characterization of Analog-to-Digital Converters (ADCs), which is related to the electronics and electrical engineering (cs.ET) sub-category. Finally, the paper discusses the vulnerability of smartphone microphones to signal injection attacks, which falls under the human-computer interaction (cs.HC) sub-category.
